During a press briefing, White House spokesperson Raj Shah addressed several topics. He expressed condolences for the victims of the tragic fire at a shopping mall in Siberia. He also announced the expulsion of Russian intelligence officers and the closure of the Russian consulate in Seattle, in response to Russia's use of a military-grade chemical weapon in the UK. Shah stated that these actions were taken in conjunction with allies and partners around the world to reduce Russia's ability to spy on Americans and threaten national security. He also mentioned that President Trump will be meeting with the leaders of Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania to celebrate their independence and discuss ways to strengthen partnerships. Shah mentioned the upcoming White House Easter Egg Roll and invited members of the White House Press Corps to bring their children. He also addressed questions about recent personnel changes, the Stormy Daniels incident, the President's approach to Russia, and other topics.